Returns a comparator that only considers time fields. Date is ignored.

The time-zone is considered when using this comparator. The input millis are truncated to be within the day in the time-zone of that input value. Thus, two inputs with different time-zones will typically not be equal @return a comparator over all time fields

Returns a comparator that only considers date fields. Time of day is ignored.

The time-zone is considered when using this comparator. The input millis are rounded down to the start of the day in the time-zone of that input value. Thus, two inputs with different time-zones will typically not be equal @return a comparator over all date fields
